02:19.560 --> 02:22.480
So who are you
thinking of for deputy SIOs?

02:23.880 --> 02:25.960
I'm not exactly spoiled for choice.

02:31.080 --> 02:32.120
Just answer.

02:34.240 --> 02:35.280
Brink...

02:38.560 --> 02:40.680
..and McElroy.

02:40.680 --> 02:42.880
McElroy?

02:42.880 --> 02:45.400
Good. That's good.

02:48.160 --> 02:49.280
MOBILE PHONE RINGS

02:50.760 --> 02:51.960
Burns.

02:54.840 --> 02:56.320
We'll be right there.

02:58.880 --> 03:01.440
There's been a fatal shooting.

03:01.440 --> 03:03.200
A police officer.

03:03.200 --> 03:05.240
We should get you
issued with a firearm.

03:05.240 --> 03:06.640
Book yourself in at the range.

03:06.640 --> 03:07.760
I don't have time.

03:07.760 --> 03:10.240
This is Belfast.

03:10.240 --> 03:11.680
Make time.

04:12.400 --> 04:15.280
I really don't want these
pictures to end up in the press.

04:15.280 --> 04:18.000
'The site can memorialise
the account.

04:18.000 --> 04:20.839
'That restricts profile access to
confirmed friends and family

04:20.839 --> 04:23.720
'but means people can still write
on Sarah's wall in remembrance.'

04:23.720 --> 04:27.240
I'd rather her father sent
in a formal request as next of kin

04:27.240 --> 04:29.080
and closed it down completely.

04:29.080 --> 04:32.560
'Yes I understand, ma'am.
I'll talk to him.'

04:32.560 --> 04:34.000
Right.

04:34.000 --> 04:35.720
Great, thank you.

04:40.400 --> 04:43.800
I spoke to Ian Kay about Friday
night's visit.

04:43.800 --> 04:47.960
He understands that it
was his daughter's decision not to

04:47.960 --> 04:49.600
take further action,

04:49.600 --> 04:54.080
so, if we can keep it out of the
press I think you're in the clear.

04:57.040 --> 04:58.760
Thank you, ma'am.

05:02.000 --> 05:05.280
I don't know whether you know that
there's been a shooting?

05:05.280 --> 05:07.040
A male police officer.

05:07.040 --> 05:09.360
I heard.

05:09.360 --> 05:12.240
Do you know him?
It's James Olson, ma'am.

05:12.240 --> 05:15.240
The Detective we saw
near the Falls Road on Sunday night.

05:19.280 --> 05:21.760
What happened?

05:21.760 --> 05:24.800
He was shot in the street outside
his house.

05:24.800 --> 05:27.320
Apparently it looks
like an assassination.

05:30.160 --> 05:31.720
I just wanted to say....

05:33.880 --> 05:36.920
..when I collected your things
from your hotel room,

05:36.920 --> 05:40.320
there were signs that you'd
had company.

05:40.320 --> 05:42.000
That a man had been there.

05:43.240 --> 05:46.280
I wanted you to know that
I removed those signs.

05:52.160 --> 05:54.880
Anything else? No, ma'am.

05:58.080 --> 05:59.720
Thank you.

06:15.480 --> 06:16.960
CROWD CHATTERS

06:18.160 --> 06:20.280
Mister Burns.

06:20.280 --> 06:23.320
Can you confirm that it's a police
officer that's been killed?

06:23.320 --> 06:26.400
Has anyone claimed
responsibility for the shooting?

06:26.400 --> 06:28.960
Doesn't James Olson live round here?

06:28.960 --> 06:33.440
Move everyone back to the corner.
Seal off the entire street!

06:50.480 --> 06:52.760
Where's his family? Inside.

07:00.080 --> 07:01.600
Close this off.

07:10.200 --> 07:12.000
WOMAN SOBS

07:19.680 --> 07:20.800
SOBBING CONTINUES

07:36.440 --> 07:39.360
Can I call Mummy? She's at work.

07:43.520 --> 07:46.000
Why do you want
to call her?

07:46.000 --> 07:48.520
To say good morning.

07:48.520 --> 07:50.040
OK.

08:11.120 --> 08:14.080
'God so loved us that he
gave himself up for us.

08:14.080 --> 08:16.520
'That is the message of the Cross.

08:16.520 --> 08:20.080
'The mystery of death and of glory.

08:20.080 --> 08:22.120
'The cross reminds us
that there is no

08:22.120 --> 08:26.360
'true love without suffering, there
is no gift of life without pain.'

08:29.160 --> 08:31.560
'God so loved us that he
gave himself up for us.

08:31.560 --> 08:36.360
'That is the message of the Cross.
The mystery of death and of glory.

08:36.360 --> 08:40.280
'The Cross reminds us that there
is no true love without suffering.

08:40.280 --> 08:44.480
'There is no gift of life
without pain.

08:44.480 --> 08:46.880
'God so loved us that he
gave himself up for us.

08:46.880 --> 08:49.160
'That is the message of the Cross.'

08:49.160 --> 08:51.840
REPORTER ON TV: And the funeral
is on Saturday.

08:51.840 --> 08:54.640
MAN ON TV: It's a small affair for
immediate family and friends.

08:54.640 --> 08:59.400
But we are also planning a memorial
service to honour Alice's memory...

08:59.400 --> 09:01.200
MAN MUMBLES ANGRILY

09:06.600 --> 09:09.360
HE SPEAKS GERMAN

09:09.360 --> 09:12.960
There's been an accident.
Fucking accident.

09:34.400 --> 09:35.600
It was an accident?

09:35.600 --> 09:37.560
Go back in there, sir.
Go back in inside.

09:37.560 --> 09:41.720
THEY SPEAK GERMAN

09:41.720 --> 09:43.680
Get some coffee down
your friend, sir.

09:45.440 --> 09:48.120
You're going to be OK,
you're going to be OK.

09:48.120 --> 09:49.160
Oh, my God!

09:49.160 --> 09:51.680
It's all right, she's going to be
OK. Don't get hysterical.

09:51.680 --> 09:52.840
Here, take her.

10:06.040 --> 10:07.320
Where the fuck are you?

10:07.320 --> 10:09.400
I could do with some
fucking help here.

10:09.400 --> 10:11.320
DCI Matthew Eastwood.
Who is this, please?

10:20.720 --> 10:24.200
PHONE: 'Your call has been forwarded
to the mobile voice system...'

10:35.440 --> 10:37.480
You should arrest him.

10:37.480 --> 10:39.560
She must have said something.
Done something.

10:40.960 --> 10:42.920
She gets beaten up
and it's her fault?

10:42.920 --> 10:44.080
Not now, OK?

10:44.080 --> 10:45.640
He's a sadistic German pig.

10:45.640 --> 10:46.680
Not now!

10:47.920 --> 10:51.400
SHE SPEAKS RUSSIAN

10:51.400 --> 10:53.000
It's Rob Breedlove.

10:53.000 --> 10:55.400
'Where are you? I've been trying
to get hold of you.'

10:55.400 --> 10:57.520
I was asleep. What's wrong?

10:57.520 --> 11:00.720
'Then you haven't heard.
It's Jimmy.'

11:00.720 --> 11:02.720
'Jimmy Olson.'

11:02.720 --> 11:04.400
KNOCK AT DOOR

11:04.400 --> 11:06.080
Come in.

11:11.080 --> 11:12.720
What the fuck's going on out there?

11:12.720 --> 11:15.640
Your German friend has just
beaten up another girl.

11:15.640 --> 11:17.240
Badly?

11:17.240 --> 11:19.440
Split her lip. Marked her face.

11:19.440 --> 11:20.680
Christ.

11:21.840 --> 11:25.680
Jimmy Olson's been shot dead.
Right outside his home.

11:25.680 --> 11:26.720
I just called him.

11:28.280 --> 11:30.560
Another police officer
answered his phone.

11:30.560 --> 11:31.640
What phone did you use?

11:33.320 --> 11:34.400
I've dealt with it.

11:56.840 --> 11:58.520
Make sure you eat all your lunch.

11:58.520 --> 11:59.840
I will.

11:59.840 --> 12:02.400
I put in lots of crunchy
black beetles. Yummy!

12:02.400 --> 12:04.680
I love you. Love you, daddy.

12:15.000 --> 12:16.560
Take her here.

12:16.560 --> 12:17.680
Get her patched up.

12:18.800 --> 12:20.000
Pick her up later on.

12:20.000 --> 12:21.320
This bullshit has got to stop.

12:21.320 --> 12:23.040
I thought that's what
you were here for.

12:25.600 --> 12:26.880
Get this place cleaned up.

12:32.880 --> 12:34.400
Come on! Hurry the fuck up!

12:36.520 --> 12:39.440
He drills and it's in,
drills and it's in. And again.

12:39.440 --> 12:42.160
No response. Where's the boys.
Nobody to be seen.

12:42.160 --> 12:44.400
Just keeps on going and going.
That's the way it went.

12:46.000 --> 12:48.920
As you may have heard,
we're setting up a Task Force.

12:48.920 --> 12:50.960
I'm going to need a right-hand man.

12:50.960 --> 12:52.600
I'd like it to be you.

12:52.600 --> 12:55.880
It would mean to start right away.
No going home, no sleep.

13:01.600 --> 13:03.080
OK.

13:03.080 --> 13:05.440
I've been told that
I need to carry a firearm,

13:05.440 --> 13:08.200
so you'll need to book me in
at the range.

13:08.200 --> 13:09.600
Maybe tomorrow morning.

13:09.600 --> 13:12.520
And I doubt I'll get back
to the hotel very much.

13:12.520 --> 13:15.280
I'd like to find out where the
nearest pool is so I can swim.

13:17.800 --> 13:18.840
Good.

13:22.720 --> 13:25.800
I've been on to HQ.
We have a list of operational names.

13:27.280 --> 13:28.560
Eden.

13:28.560 --> 13:30.280
A place where the
woman gets the blame.

13:30.280 --> 13:32.240
Top Hat. Too posh.

13:32.240 --> 13:34.360
Alamo. Too Texan.

13:34.360 --> 13:35.640
Musicman.

13:35.640 --> 13:37.080
Too male.

13:37.080 --> 13:38.280
Genesis.

13:38.280 --> 13:41.200
My least favourite band.
Well, aside from U2.

13:41.200 --> 13:42.240
Hey, steady on...

13:42.240 --> 13:43.480
Ashdown.

13:43.480 --> 13:44.720
Too foresty.

13:44.720 --> 13:45.800
What?

13:45.800 --> 13:47.160
Reminds me of shallow graves.

13:49.080 --> 13:50.520
Seriousity, gentlemen.

14:09.760 --> 14:11.440
Good morning.

14:11.440 --> 14:12.520
ALL: Morning.

14:12.520 --> 14:15.760
First things first.
All telephones disconnected.

14:15.760 --> 14:19.520
All mobile phones switched to
a silent mode or switched off.

14:22.560 --> 14:24.880
Welcome to Operation Musicman.

14:24.880 --> 14:27.560
MOBILE RINGS

14:27.560 --> 14:28.600
Hmm?

14:28.600 --> 14:29.640
Where are you?

14:29.640 --> 14:31.160
Yeah, I'm here. I'm in the car park.

14:31.160 --> 14:32.240
She's started.

14:32.240 --> 14:33.720
All right.

14:33.720 --> 14:37.360
As many of you will be aware,
we have come to the conclusion

14:37.360 --> 14:41.800
that the recent murders of Fiona
Gallagher, Alice Parker Monroe

14:41.800 --> 14:44.480
and Sarah Kay are linked...

14:45.560 --> 14:47.880
..and the work of a serial offender.

14:47.880 --> 14:51.680
Anyone in any doubt about the gender
of the person responsible?

14:54.720 --> 14:57.480
Then let's not waste our time
looking for a woman.

14:57.480 --> 15:01.240
I've asked my two deputies,
Garrett Brink and Jerry McElroy,

15:01.240 --> 15:02.960
to take responsibility
for allocating

15:02.960 --> 15:04.920
all the key roles within
the Task Force.

15:04.920 --> 15:07.480
They will also lead the debrief
on the Sarah Kay murder.

15:17.200 --> 15:20.600
When you hear the pathologist's
report, you will learn that

15:20.600 --> 15:24.720
Sarah Kay was six to seven weeks
pregnant at the time of her death.

15:24.720 --> 15:26.280
MOBILE PLAYS: "In Da Club"
by 50 Cent

15:26.280 --> 15:27.560
♪ Go, shawty

15:27.560 --> 15:28.720
♪ It's your birthday

15:28.720 --> 15:30.400
♪ We gon' party like it's your
birthday

15:30.400 --> 15:32.800
♪ We gon' sip Bacardi
Like it's your birthday

15:32.800 --> 15:35.560
♪ And you know we don't give a
It's not your birthday!

15:35.560 --> 15:38.440
♪ You can find me in the club
Bottle full of bub... ♪

15:38.440 --> 15:41.720
That fact is not to leave this room.

15:45.400 --> 15:47.560
Do you think she noticed I was late?

15:47.560 --> 15:48.760
I think you got away with it.

15:48.760 --> 15:50.280
Good.

15:50.280 --> 15:53.160
Think of it as an addiction.

15:53.160 --> 15:56.320
There's a law of diminishing
returns.

15:56.320 --> 15:58.320
The serialist,
like the heroin addict,

15:58.320 --> 16:00.800
is always seeking
that elusive first high,

16:02.040 --> 16:03.440
and he's doomed to fail.

16:05.960 --> 16:09.040
That's why the cooling off periods
get shorter,

16:09.040 --> 16:12.360
and the crimes become
more elaborate.

16:15.040 --> 16:20.320
And he will carry on feeding
that killing habit...

16:22.040 --> 16:23.880
..unless we stop him.

16:29.840 --> 16:32.800
He clearly has a victim type.

16:32.800 --> 16:36.840
They are not victims of chance,
they are victims of choice.

16:36.840 --> 16:39.840
They don't know him,
but he knows them.

16:39.840 --> 16:44.040
It's possible that he's out there
stalking his next victim now.

16:44.040 --> 16:45.760
He may even have a waiting list.

16:47.600 --> 16:50.880
It seems that he breaks into
their homes a day or two

16:50.880 --> 16:52.760
before he then returns to kill them.

16:54.320 --> 16:56.800
How does he find
and select his victims?

16:58.640 --> 17:00.480
We need to be looking
at correspondences.

17:03.480 --> 17:05.520
What links these three women?

17:08.359 --> 17:11.640
We will be making an announcement
to the press later this afternoon.

17:11.640 --> 17:13.599
There's every possibility
after we do that,

17:13.599 --> 17:15.440
that we will be flooded with calls.

17:16.520 --> 17:21.000
But all of those calls need to be
captured, recorded and assessed.

17:23.040 --> 17:26.119
For there are many of us gathered
here today with still more to come.

17:26.119 --> 17:27.520
There is only one of him.

17:29.040 --> 17:31.360
You'd think that gives us
the advantage.

17:32.840 --> 17:33.880
But it doesn't.

17:35.480 --> 17:39.880
He moves around on his own,
in darkness.

17:41.760 --> 17:44.440
And we operate under the glare
of media lights.

17:46.400 --> 17:48.880
Now let's make sure that
we don't let anything

17:48.880 --> 17:50.880
slip through the cracks.

17:50.880 --> 17:53.960
The Devil, quite literally,
ladies and gentlemen...

17:55.240 --> 17:56.360
..is in the detail.

17:57.720 --> 18:01.120
Detail, detail and detail again.

18:08.840 --> 18:10.000
Can I help you?

18:13.960 --> 18:15.680
You!!

18:15.680 --> 18:16.920
Looking for someone?

18:20.960 --> 18:22.760
Are you talking to me?

18:22.760 --> 18:24.080
Yes, I'm taking to you.

18:25.560 --> 18:27.320
What are you doing here?

18:27.320 --> 18:28.840
How is that any
business of yours?

18:28.840 --> 18:30.640
I'm making it my business.

18:30.640 --> 18:31.920
You're not from around here.

18:33.120 --> 18:35.280
So? So what are you doing?

18:35.280 --> 18:37.360
There's a name tag
on the front seat.

18:37.360 --> 18:39.320
Hey, that stuff is private.

18:45.120 --> 18:47.240
I doubt James would be that
thrilled to know

18:47.240 --> 18:49.320
you're looking at his
family's case files.

18:49.320 --> 18:50.840
Jimmy?

18:50.840 --> 18:52.960
I'm a grief counsellor.

18:52.960 --> 18:54.200
He lost his son, Daniel.

18:54.200 --> 18:55.240
I know he did.

19:01.080 --> 19:02.280
You're on the wrong road.

19:03.720 --> 19:06.240
Yeah, I realise that now.

19:07.520 --> 19:09.920
Turn around and go back up there
and take the next right.

19:56.400 --> 19:57.600
For fuck's sake.

20:39.080 --> 20:40.120
Mr Spector?

20:41.120 --> 20:42.160
I was in the area.

20:43.800 --> 20:47.800
I was worried you missed a session
but, er, if this is a bad time?

20:47.800 --> 20:49.640
No. Come on in.

21:19.640 --> 21:21.520
VOICEMAIL: 'You have
one new message.'

21:21.520 --> 21:23.400
'Morning, Mummy. It's only me.'

21:24.400 --> 21:26.520
'I'm about to leave for school.'

21:26.520 --> 21:30.560
'I hope you're OK and all the babies
are OK, too. Love you. Bye!'

21:37.800 --> 21:41.520
When Daniel was small,
I was a registered childminder.

21:45.160 --> 21:46.960
They all used to play out there.

21:48.080 --> 21:49.840
Daniel, and the kids I looked after.

21:56.400 --> 21:59.960
When Jim went to prison
they revoked my licence.

22:06.000 --> 22:07.080
I've been into his room.

22:10.320 --> 22:11.360
Good.

22:12.640 --> 22:14.040
Would you like to see it?

22:18.440 --> 22:23.160
Stella, this is Martina Dean.
Martina is our Media Liaison
Officer.

22:23.160 --> 22:25.720
Before we start, I need a word
with you in private, sir.

22:38.960 --> 22:40.480
It's nothing special, is it?

22:49.640 --> 22:52.080
I don't think I'll ever be able
to accept what's happened.

22:56.720 --> 22:57.760
You don't have to.

22:58.800 --> 23:00.760
I don't subscribe to
that model of grief.

23:02.480 --> 23:06.440
I don't see bereavement as ever
being resolved or accepted.

23:08.680 --> 23:12.120
There is no closure, no recovery.

23:13.560 --> 23:15.280
But you can learn to live a life

23:15.280 --> 23:17.760
without the physical
presence of your son.

23:21.560 --> 23:22.680
That's just it.

23:26.320 --> 23:27.360
I can't.

23:32.040 --> 23:34.840
He would always come to me
for kisses and cuddles.

23:39.160 --> 23:40.800
He would always hold my hand.

23:45.360 --> 23:47.440
All I want is for somebody
to hold me.

23:50.320 --> 23:53.480
Tell me I'm going to be all right.
That I'm not going mad.

24:12.080 --> 24:13.120
Would you do that?

24:15.960 --> 24:17.560
What?

24:17.560 --> 24:18.600
Hold me?

24:25.560 --> 24:26.600
Yes.

24:58.080 --> 25:00.080
He came to my hotel room.

25:00.080 --> 25:01.520
When?

25:01.520 --> 25:02.520
Sunday night.

25:03.760 --> 25:04.840
Monday morning.

25:06.920 --> 25:07.960
Why?

25:17.240 --> 25:18.280
What time?

25:20.520 --> 25:22.120
Between 2.30 and 4.30am.

25:24.160 --> 25:26.520
About the same time that Sarah Kay
was being murdered.

25:29.520 --> 25:30.920
So he's on the hotel CCTV?

25:31.960 --> 25:33.120
Probably.

25:36.760 --> 25:39.280
Did you talk about his case?

25:39.280 --> 25:40.320
Or your review?

25:42.240 --> 25:43.280
No.

25:48.960 --> 25:50.840
James Olson was a married man,
Stella.

25:52.080 --> 25:54.440
Married, two kids.

25:55.520 --> 25:56.760
That's his business.

25:59.080 --> 26:00.840
He wasn't wearing a ring.

26:00.840 --> 26:04.200
I'm sure that'll be of some comfort
to his wife when she finds out

26:04.200 --> 26:07.160
that her husband spent his last
night on earth in your bed!

26:09.240 --> 26:10.560
You were a married man.

26:12.160 --> 26:13.920
When you spent a night in my bed.

26:21.200 --> 26:24.480
Am I going to regret my decision
to make you head of this Task Force?

26:26.040 --> 26:27.080
I hope not.

26:28.880 --> 26:31.080
Did you deliberately withhold
this information

26:31.080 --> 26:32.800
until after the debriefing?

26:32.800 --> 26:35.920
Yes. But I thought you should
know before the press conference.

26:38.480 --> 26:44.280
An SIO should display
high levels of personal integrity.

26:45.560 --> 26:50.760
Demonstrate professional,
ethical and moral standards!

26:50.760 --> 26:52.880
Show some self-control!

26:54.360 --> 26:55.760
I wasn't SIO at the time.

27:03.000 --> 27:05.760
Are you in the least bit upset
that Olson is dead?

27:08.240 --> 27:09.920
Shall we get Martina back in here?

27:25.640 --> 27:28.080
"I know where you live?"
"I know where you live?"

27:28.080 --> 27:29.240
You scumbag piece of shit!

27:29.240 --> 27:31.200
Did something happen
to your friend?

27:31.200 --> 27:33.720
Oh, I am sorry to hear about that.
Get off me!

27:33.720 --> 27:36.440
I'm a police officer, for God's
sake!

27:36.440 --> 27:37.960
Do wish him a speedy recovery.

27:40.760 --> 27:42.320
Get off me.

27:42.320 --> 27:45.920
